-- European Commission: broker ICAP may have broken EU antitrust rules
-- 
-- Tue Jun 10, 2014 05:52AM EDT
-- None



BRUSSELS, June 10 (Reuters) - The European Commission has told broker ICAP <IAP.L> that it may have broken antitrust rules by facilitating cartels for interest-rate yen derivatives, the European Union's antitrust enforcer said on Tuesday.

"The Commission has concerns that ICAP may have been involved in cartels concerning yen interest rate derivatives as a facilitator," it said in a statement.